<HEADLINE>
FT  21 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Reduced deficit at JW Spear
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
JW Spear, the Enfield-based toys and games manufacturer, reported sharply
reduced losses in its seasonally unfavourable first half.
Losses before tax were Pounds 315,000 for the six months to <DATE>June 30</DATE>, down
from Pounds 638,000 at the same stage of <DATE>1991</DATE>. The group, famed for its
Scrabble game, achieved profits of Pounds 2.53m pre-tax in the full <DATE>1991</DATE>
year.
The outcome reflected lower interest payable of Pounds 5,000 (Pounds
125,000). Turnover was marginally lower at Pounds 8.28m as <LOCATION>France</LOCATION> proved a
'lacklustre' market following the impact of video games, said <PERSON>Mr Francis
Spear</PERSON>, chairman.
Losses per share were cut to 5.78p (8.19p) and the interim dividend goes up
to 2.5p (2p).
</TEXT>
