FT  03 JUN 94 / UK Company News: J W Spear search for white knight
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Advisers to Scrabble maker J W Spear were <TIME>last night</TIME> still searching for a
white knight to top the Pounds 47m bid for the company from US toy giant
<ORGANIZATION>Hasbro</ORGANIZATION>.
But it looked increasingly unlikely that their efforts would be successful
ahead of <TIME>this morning</TIME>'s deadline when acceptances from Spear family trusts
owning 24.9 per cent of the shares become irrevocable.
<ORGANIZATION>Hasbro</ORGANIZATION> already has a 26.7 per cent stake in Spear acquired four years ago.
Barings has asked the Spear trustees to forward a letter to the
beneficiaries which questions why the bid should be accepted, given that all
the <ORGANIZATION>Spear</ORGANIZATION> board, barring the chairman <PERSON>Francis Spear</PERSON>, believe it is
inadequate.
</TEXT>
