let the computer play, then I played against the computer. Then I let the
computer compete with itself.;    <ORGANIZATION>Scramble</ORGANIZATION> is for computers that have <ORGANIZATION>EGA</ORGANIZATION> or
VGA video cards and monitors only. It works best with a mouse, but folks with
just a keyboard may play, too. Players may add to its dictionary, and in
general you get all the features of Scrabble without having to hunt down the
tiles. Scramble may be registered for <MONEY>$15</MONEY> from <ORGANIZATION>Tud Gruber Software</ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION>P.O.</LOCATION> Box
13408, <LOCATION>Las Vegas</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Nev.</LOCATION>, 89112.;    TIKLER -- If you're as tired as I am of
sticking yellow reminders on your phone, your PC and your cat, here's a very
nice little reminder and appointment program.;    Tikler lets you specify how
many days in advance you want to be reminded about anything from birthdays to
job interviews. You may edit entries, delete them, see past appointments and
even look into the future. Even if you're not familiar with how these programs
work, you'll be up and running shortly after you copy the files. Tikler gives
you password security, and it allows you to print your appointments. If you
know you have an appointment tomorrow with your boss, but you've forgotten
when, simply search for "boss" and your appointment will pop up on the
screen.;    You can put Tikler in your autoexec.bat so that it's the first
thing to pop up when you boot up in the <TIME>morning</TIME>. It will work with monochrome
or color monitors and it will work fine on floppy or hard disk. To register,
send <MONEY>$15</MONEY> to <PERSON>Olsen Outdoors</PERSON>, 68 <LOCATION>Hartwell Ave.</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Littleton</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Mass.</LOCATION>, 01460.  </TEXT>
